Flask-mail provides simple integration with TurboMail.

Full TurboMail docs here:

Sample usage:

from flask import Flask
from flaskext.mail import init_mail, Message

app = Flask(__name__)
init_mail(app)

@app.route("/")
def index():
    msg = Message(subject="hello",
                  sender="me@here.com",
                  recipients=["you@there.com"])

    msg.plain = "hello"
    msg.send()

Configuration

There are 2 ways to configure this extension:

1. By providing a "mail.cfg" file. You can override the filename
using the MAIL_CONFIG_FILENAME in your Flask configuration.

2. Passing a dict of settings as second argument to init_mail.




